<doc id="869622" wikidata="Q5154503" url="?curid=869622" title="Communist Unity Groups (Sweden)">
<text>Kommunistiska Enhetsgrupperna () was a section that left &quot;Kommunistiska Partiet Marxist-Leninisterna (revolutionärerna)&quot; in 1975. KEG considered that KPML(r):s politics towards the trade unions was ultra-leftist and sectarian. KEG was dissolved in 1977, and most of the members later joined SKP.

The KEG group in Stockholm, &quot;Stockholms Kommunistiska Enhetsgrupp&quot;, continued to exist until 1979. In that year SKEG merged with the Communist Association of Norrköping to form SKF-ml.

KEG published &quot;Enhet&quot; (&#x27;Unity&#x27;) 1975–1977.

