<doc id="869735" wikidata="Q1939364" url="?curid=869735" title="Supergrass (album)">
<text>Supergrass is the third studio album by the English alternative rock band Supergrass. It was released in the UK on 20 September 1999 and reached #3. It is often referred to as &quot;the X-ray album&quot;, due to the picture on the sleeve. In Australia a free CD was included with some live tracks. In 2022, the album was remastered and reissued as a 2CD deluxe edition, which includes new remixes of several of the songs created by John Leckie and John Cornfield among other bonus tracks.

==Track listing==

All tracks written by Supergrass/Rob Coombes.

